tldr: The agent implemented a database for questionnaire responses, an admin
  dashboard with CSV export, and a simplified password-based authentication
  system using Next.js middleware. The database was set up with NeonDB and
  Prisma, and the application was prepared for testing.
overview: The user initiated a project to build a Sleep Questionnaire
  Application, providing a Statement of Work. The agent evaluated the existing
  codebase, identifying the need for a database to store questionnaire
  responses, an admin dashboard for data access, and an authentication system.
  After clarifying requirements for a simple password-based authentication and
  specific demographic data, the agent developed a comprehensive plan. This plan
  included updating demographic fields, creating a Prisma model for
  questionnaire responses, implementing API endpoints for data submission,
  retrieval, and CSV export, and building an admin dashboard with login
  functionality. A key decision was to simplify the authentication system by
  leveraging Next.js middleware for route protection and a basic cookie-based
  session, which streamlined the codebase. The agent then guided the user
  through setting up the NeonDB database, configuring environment variables, and
  running Prisma migrations. Finally, the agent began testing the implemented
  features by submitting a questionnaire response through the browser.
